sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1855001
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Iain Galpin
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: A fusion protein of a transmembrane domain (Lpp-OmpA) and a zinc-finger domain (sZF2),under pL_lac promotion and containing a C-terminal FLAG tag. It is used to exhibit a zinc-finger dsDNA binding domain complimentary to TGCTGCTTC on the cell surface of E.coli.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: We had to optimise the codon for E.coli K12, and then alter the codon slightly to remove unwanted cut sites. The Lpp-OmpA domain is preceeded by an NdeI cut site, and followed by an AgeI cut site. The sZF2 domain is preceeded by an NheI cut site and followed by a ClaI cut site.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Lpp-OmpA is originally from E.coli; sZF2 is from http://www.nature.com/nmeth/journal/v10/n5/abs/nmeth.2407.html

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: trkD
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: trkD, a functional Kup (formerly TrkD) system took up Cs+ with a moderate rate and affinity
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Zilong WANG, Yi ZHENG
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Escherichia coli cells which contain a functional Kup (formerly TrkD) system took up Cs' with a moderate rate and affinity. Kup is a separate K+ uptake system with relatively little discrimination in the transport of the cations K+, Rb+, and Cs'. Regardless of the presence or absence of Kup, K+-replete cells took up Cs'primarily by a very low affinity mode, proportional to the ratio of the Cs' and K+ concentrations in the medium. In our project, trkD is used to collect Cs-137 when recN is activated by radiation and start the transcription of trkD,in order to absorb this kind of radioactive source like Cs-137

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K2110003
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Le He
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This gene encodes the terephthalic acid(TPA) transporting protein. TPA is not a kind of nutrient substance for most organisms, including common chassis organisms like E.coli and Saccharomyces cerevisiae. However, as a kind of TPA degradable organism, RhodococcusjostiiRHA1 can transport TPA into their cells because of the TPA transporting protein genetpaK in their genome. This gene is also verified to be useful in Saccharomyces cerevisiae.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: It comes from the genome of RhodococcusjostiiRHA1.
